    <!--
    - Main Apptentive Styling item info

    - Have a style named "ApptentiveThemeOverride" in your styles.xml file to override Apptentive styles
    - Items defined in this style will ONLY affect Apptentive interactions

    - We disable the android:background style for Apptentive interaction styling
    - It causes some unexpected issues for some Views
    - You can re-enable this within ApptentiveThemeOverride

    - Material Color info: https://material.io/blog/android-material-theme-color

    Dialogs:
    - Dialog background color uses colorSurface
    - Dialog color on background (title and message text) uses colorOnSurface
    - Dialog buttons text color uses colorPrimary
    - Dialog title has an alpha of .90 by default
        - Override with apptentiveHeaderAlpha
    - Dialog message has an alpha of .75 by default
        - Override with apptentiveSubheaderAlpha

    Surveys:
    - Survey toolbar / bottom bar colors uses colorPrimary
    - Survey toolbar / bottom bar text colors uses colorOnPrimary
    - Survey background uses android:colorBackground
    - Survey color on background (text & some widget colors) uses colorOnBackground
    - Survey submit button color uses colorPrimary
    - Survey submit button text color uses colorOnPrimary
    - Survey description, question title, and radio/checkbox options have alphas of .90 by default
        - Override with apptentiveHeaderAlpha
        - Note that affects default text colors as well as error colors
    - Question instructions, text box hints, and range labels have an alpha of .75 by default
        - Override with apptentiveSubheaderAlpha
        - Note that affects default text colors as well as error colors

    Use Survey header image instead of title text:
    - Set through styles apptentiveSurveyTitleStyle & apptentiveSurveyHeaderImageStyle
    - Example (Good starting point):

    <style name="ApptentiveThemeOverride">
        <item name="apptentiveSurveyTitleStyle">@style/Custom.Survey.Title</item>
        <item name="apptentiveSurveyHeaderImageStyle">@style/Custom.Survey.HeaderImage</item>
    </style>

    <style name="Custom.Survey.Title" parent="Widget.MaterialComponents.TextView">
        <item name="android:visibility">gone</item> <- So the title text doesn't show
    </style>

    <style name="Custom.Survey.HeaderImage">
        <item name="android:src">@drawable/example_logo</item> <- Set your header image here
        <item name="android:maxHeight">?actionBarSize</item> <- minHeight/maxHeight to size
        <item name="android:adjustViewBounds">true</item> <- Helps with image resizing
        <item name="android:layout_gravity">center</item> <- Image positioning
        <item name="android:layout_margin">2dp</item> <- Image spacing
    </style>
    -->

